      "body" : "Think of this in the real world. \r\n\r\n Spending something you donÃ¢ÂÂt have is obviously not possible. So why not simply say the following: \r\n\r\n\r\nADVANCED: \r\n\r\n[ ] Allow spending of unconfirmed changed.\r\n\r\n (leaving the flag off by default).\r\n \r\nYou are not going to explain this adequately in 5 lines or less Ã¢ÂÂ especially to nubs  .. so why bother ? Let them that wish to use it, RTFM some and then its caveat emptor if they flip it on.\r\n\r\n",
